Nigeria’s State Security Service Holds 2 Suspects Over UN Building Blast

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-08-31T12:37:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/nigeria-s-state-security-service-holds-2-suspects-over-un-building-blast.html
(Corrects to show one suspect being sought in second
paragraph.)  Nigeria’s State Security Service is
holding two suspects in connection with the bombing of a United
Nations building in the country’s capital, Abuja, spokeswoman
Marilyn Ogar said.  One suspect, the person that may have led the attack that
killed 23 people and wounded 71 on Aug. 26, is still being
sought, Ogar said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  